<item>
            <title>[SPARK-16304] LinkageError should not crash Spark executor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-16304</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we have a linkage error in the user code, Spark executors get killed immediately. This is not great for user experience, especially in shared environments in which multiple applications are multiplexed through one context.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12985241">SPARK-16304</key>
            <summary>LinkageError should not crash Spark executor</summary>
